      "note_no": "70",
      "note": "Thus, contrary to the Biblical account, Joseph is stated here to have disclosed his identity to Benjamin long before he revealed himself to his ten half-brothers. The words \"their past doings\" obviously refer to their treacherous behaviour towards himself which Joseph had now presumably disclosed to Benjamin."
